    {
      "id": "sqlserver-cluster-subops-guarded",
      "service": "database/sqlserver",
      "enabled": true,
      "heavy": true,
      "_note": "COVERAGE-ONLY guarded lifecycle for the sqlserver DBaaS cluster sub-op WRITE endpoints (incl. the sqlserver-only create/delete cluster which the shared heavy-shared-dbaas lifecycle EXCLUDES because SQL Server needs a real license). Soft-captures an existing cluster_id (+ instance_group_id/bsg_id/log_type) from read-only calls; absent that, tokens normalize to the catalog '*' key so every endpoint is CALLED+RECORDED (4xx counts). All mutating steps optional+grouped+broad-expect_status; heavy:true (SCP_RUN_HEAVY); DELETEs destructive:true. Bodies from api_docs request_example, UNPROVEN. sqlserver DIVERGES from the relational template: it has add-secondary (HA standby, needs a license) and databases (add/del DB list) and has NO archive/replicas/promote/other-region/reset-replica/sync-replica-state endpoints.",
